A taxi driver had a lucky escape today when he misjudged a bend and drove straight through a wall, leaving his car balanced precariously above another road.  

The Volkswagen Passat was tottering over the 10ft drop for hours after the crash in Birmingham around 2am this morning.  

The taxi was apparently driving down a hill on Gas Street, near the city centre, when the driver failed to anticipate the sharp turn and carried on through the wall.  

