The streets were shut for three hours while the area was made safe, and the pavement below the crash scene was covered in piles of bricks.  

The driver was taken to hospital to be treated, but was discharged around 10am.  

Pedestrian Sarah Morris, who passed by the scene shortly after the crash, posted on twitter: 'Excuse my language... But s***!  

'That would be a car smashed through the wall at the bottom of Gas Street. Clearly didn't slow down for the corner.'  

