A spokesperson for West Midlands Ambulance Service added: 'We received a call just before 2.10am to reports of a car of a car in collision with a wall.

'We sent one ambulance and an ambulance driver, by the time they arrived the driver was already out of his car.  

'He was taken to Queen Elizabeth Hospital and we have no information on his condition.' 

